   Suggested Fix: this.metric = TimeSeriesParams.metricParam(m -> indexMode == IndexMode.TIME_SERIES ? null : TimeSeriesParams.MetricType.POSITION);
3. Explanation: The 'hasDocValues' parameter is set to true by default, but it should be set to false if the 'dimension' parameter is true. This can cause issues with time series data.
   Suggested Fix: this.hasDocValues = Parameter.docValuesParam(m -> dimension.getValue() == false);

